<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-10-30T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-10-30T22:00:00-05:00" n="78" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d78">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00/4279: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-10-30T21:00:00-06:00"><hi rend="italic">October 30,
                                        1928—9 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received October 31—10:50
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>128. Your telegram number 95, October 27, 5 p.m. In view of the reported
                            presence of Ferrera in western Honduras, President Paz requests as a
                            precautionary measure that the <hi rend="italic">Cleveland</hi> be
                            permitted to remain in Honduran waters for the present. However in my
                            opinion there is now no adequate reason why the ship should not depart
                            at the end of this week.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Puerto Cortez.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>